                <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/06/travel/hotels-are-enhancing-offerings-for-pint-size-guests.html" data-tracking-index="11" data-rref="">
                    <img
                        src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/09/travel/09trending-kidsclubs1/09trending-kidsclubs1-videoLarge.jpg"
                        srcset="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/09/travel/09trending-kidsclubs1/09trending-kidsclubs1-videoLarge.jpg 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/09/travel/09trending-kidsclubs1/09trending-kidsclubs1-mediumThreeByTwo440.jpg 440w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/09/travel/09trending-kidsclubs1/09trending-kidsclubs1-mediumThreeByTwo225.jpg 225w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/09/travel/09trending-kidsclubs1/09trending-kidsclubs1-hpSmall.jpg 163w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/09/travel/09trending-kidsclubs1/09trending-kidsclubs1-thumbLarge.jpg 150w"
                        alt=""
                    />
                                                        </a>
                <figcaption class="caption" itemprop="caption description">
                    <span class="credit" itemprop="copyrightHolder"><span class="visually-hidden">Credit</span>Marbella Club Hotel</span>
                </figcaption>
            </figure>
                <div class="story-body">
            <h2 class="headline">
                <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/06/travel/hotels-are-enhancing-offerings-for-pint-size-guests.html" data-tracking-index="11" data-rref="">Hotels Are Enhancing Offerings for Pint-Size Guests</a>
            </h2>
            <p class="summary">Once boring spaces with a few toys and a TV, “kids’ clubs” at hotels and resorts are evolving into destinations that your children may actually enjoy hanging out in.</p>
            <p class="byline">
                <span class="freshness"><time data-utc-timestamp="1544090400" datetime="1544090400"></time></span>
                                <span class="divider"></span>
                                <span class="author" itemprop="author">By SHIVANI VORA</span>
            </p>
        </div>
    </article>
</li>
                <li>
    <article class="story theme-summary ">
                    <h3 class="kicker">Travel Tips</h3>
                                                    <figure class="media photo" aria-label="media" role="group">
                <span class="visually-hidden">Photo</span>
                <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/04/travel/want-to-take-your-pet-on-your-next-vacation-here-is-what-you-need-to-know.html" data-tracking-index="12" data-rref="">
                    <img
                        src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/09/travel/09TIPS/merlin_147676674_3bfc6a3f-aedd-4767-9760-4a61ea0dfc6e-mediumThreeByTwo440.jpg"
                        srcset="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/09/travel/09TIPS/merlin_147676674_3bfc6a3f-aedd-4767-9760-4a61ea0dfc6e-mediumThreeByTwo440.jpg 440w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/09/travel/09TIPS/merlin_147676674_3bfc6a3f-aedd-4767-9760-4a61ea0dfc6e-mediumThreeByTwo225.jpg 225w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/09/travel/09TIPS/merlin_147676674_3bfc6a3f-aedd-4767-9760-4a61ea0dfc6e-hpSmall.jpg 163w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/09/travel/09TIPS/merlin_147676674_3bfc6a3f-aedd-4767-9760-4a61ea0dfc6e-thumbLarge.jpg 150w"
                        alt=""
                    />
                                                        </a>
                <figcaption class="caption" itemprop="caption description">
                    <span class="credit" itemprop="copyrightHolder"><span class="visually-hidden">Credit</span>Lars Leetaru</span>
                </figcaption>
            </figure>
                <div class="story-body">
            <h2 class="headline">
                <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/04/travel/want-to-take-your-pet-on-your-next-vacation-here-is-what-you-need-to-know.html" data-tracking-index="12" data-rref=""> Want to Take Your Pet on Your Next Vacation? Here Is What You Need to Know</a>
            </h2>
            <p class="summary">Is it safe? What are the rules? What to pack? The six questions you should ask before you take your pup on a plane.</p>
            <p class="byline">
                <span class="freshness"><time data-utc-timestamp="1543917606" datetime="1543917606"></time></span>
                                <span class="divider"></span>
                                <span class="author" itemprop="author">By JUSTIN SABLICH</span>
            </p>
        </div>
    </article>
</li>
                <li>
    <article class="story theme-summary ">
                    <h3 class="kicker">Travel Tips</h3>
                                                    <figure class="media photo" aria-label="media" role="group">
                <span class="visually-hidden">Photo</span>
                <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/28/travel/five-tips-to-make-traveling-with-a-food-allergy-easier.html" data-tracking-index="13" data-rref="">
                    <img
                        src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/02/travel/02TIPS/merlin_147353133_ce2a28b0-3f2f-41d6-82e3-04399fa47eb3-mediumThreeByTwo440.jpg"
                        srcset="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/02/travel/02TIPS/merlin_147353133_ce2a28b0-3f2f-41d6-82e3-04399fa47eb3-mediumThreeByTwo440.jpg 440w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/02/travel/02TIPS/merlin_147353133_ce2a28b0-3f2f-41d6-82e3-04399fa47eb3-mediumThreeByTwo225.jpg 225w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/02/travel/02TIPS/merlin_147353133_ce2a28b0-3f2f-41d6-82e3-04399fa47eb3-hpSmall.jpg 163w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/02/travel/02TIPS/merlin_147353133_ce2a28b0-3f2f-41d6-82e3-04399fa47eb3-thumbLarge.jpg 150w"
                        alt=""
                    />
                                                        </a>
                <figcaption class="caption" itemprop="caption description">
                    <span class="credit" itemprop="copyrightHolder"><span class="visually-hidden">Credit</span>Lars Leetaru</span>
                </figcaption>
            </figure>
                <div class="story-body">
            <h2 class="headline">
                <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/28/travel/five-tips-to-make-traveling-with-a-food-allergy-easier.html" data-tracking-index="13" data-rref="">Five Tips to Make Traveling With a Food Allergy Easier</a>
            </h2>
            <p class="summary">Managing a food allergy is tricky when you travel, but these precautionary steps can help you explore culinary culture and stay healthy.</p>
            <p class="byline">
                <span class="freshness"><time data-utc-timestamp="1543399208" datetime="1543399208"></time></span>
                                <span class="divider"></span>
                                <span class="author" itemprop="author">By SHIVANI VORA</span>
            </p>
        </div>
    </article>
</li>
                <li>
    <article class="story theme-summary ">
                    <h3 class="kicker">Trending</h3>
                                                    <figure class="media photo" aria-label="media" role="group">
                <span class="visually-hidden">Photo</span>
                <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/27/travel/airport-hotels-go-glam.html" data-tracking-index="14" data-rref="">
                    <img
                        src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/02/travel/02trending-airporthotels1/02trending-airporthotels1-videoLarge-v2.jpg"
                        srcset="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/02/travel/02trending-airporthotels1/02trending-airporthotels1-videoLarge-v2.jpg 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/02/travel/02trending-airporthotels1/02trending-airporthotels1-mediumThreeByTwo440-v2.jpg 440w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/02/travel/02trending-airporthotels1/02trending-airporthotels1-mediumThreeByTwo225-v2.jpg 225w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/02/travel/02trending-airporthotels1/02trending-airporthotels1-hpSmall-v2.jpg 163w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/12/02/travel/02trending-airporthotels1/02trending-airporthotels1-thumbLarge-v2.jpg 150w"
                        alt=""
                    />
                                                        </a>
                <figcaption class="caption" itemprop="caption description">
                    <span class="credit" itemprop="copyrightHolder"><span class="visually-hidden">Credit</span>Moxy Hotels</span>
                </figcaption>
            </figure>
                <div class="story-body">
            <h2 class="headline">
                <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/27/travel/airport-hotels-go-glam.html" data-tracking-index="14" data-rref="">Airport Hotels Go Glam</a>
            </h2>
            <p class="summary">Airport hotels don’t have to be purely functional and only places to sleep before or after a long flight. Increasingly, they can be fun and in some cases, even glamorous.</p>
            <p class="byline">
                <span class="freshness"><time data-utc-timestamp="1543312801" datetime="1543312801"></time></span>
                                <span class="divider"></span>
                                <span class="author" itemprop="author">By SHIVANI VORA</span>
            </p>
        </div>
    </article>
</li>
                </ol>
        </div>
                        </section>
    
    
